content.description: Climb vice grip but continue right at the lip and finish up the arete.

Start on the left side of El Parasol roof, Left hand in an incut gaston and right hand on sidepull under the roof.  Move to the slopey lip, sort out your hands, then do some tenuous foot work and punch for a good hold.  Short, cool holds, and packs a punch.
content.location: On the El Parasol Boulder which is a couple hundred feet above the North shore beach on the West bluff and slightly north.

content.description: This climbs the overhanging dihedral-like boulder below the huge roof of the El Parasol project.  Start right hand on the big undercling/pinch, and left hand on a crimp just up and left.  Make a hard move up right to a jug and follow good holds to top out.
content.location: From the parking area, walk all the way down the hill to a bench at the end of the gravel trail.  Walk straight up the hill behind the bench to the problem.

content.description: Low start to Expose Yourself where you start squeezing both aretes underneath the nose in the roof.  Great moves, a scary landing though, with a drop off on one side and pointy rocks on the other.
content.location: On the El Parasol Boulder.  A couple hundred feet above the north shore beach on the westbluff and slightly north.

content.description: What dreams are made of!Sit with a right gastoney hold and left on a glassy rail.  A crux move gains the lip and a mantle follows.
content.location: Just left of Rubik’s Cubicle and next to the fridge boulder.

content.description: From a sit or crouch on the right side of the roof, with your right hand in a good slot and left on a low undercling, pull on and climb leftwards across the lip of the roof finishing on the left side of the far arete.  The seam 2 feet above the lip was not used so instead of mantling out early you climb out the whole feature.     This is definitely one of my favorite of the grade (whatever it ends up being) I have done at the lake.
content.location: The El Parasol roof, just above the fat raccoon boulder.

content.description: This is the obvious and difficult sit start on the Fridge Boulder.  With your right hand on an undercling and your left on a crimp, pull on and do a very powerful punch to a sloper.  From there finish it out on the Fridge Direct.
content.location: Just above Fat Raccoon on the Fridge Boulder.

content.description: From the obvious rail at the bottom of the roof and an edge just left of it, climb left into Vice Grip and finish as for that problem.  Likely the first V13 in Wisconsin and one of the hardest in the Midwest.
This is in the el parasol roof.  The start is pictured, link into Midwest Dream.  The big move on Midwest Dream is a bit heady, do be careful.
content.location: In the el parasol roof just above the fat raccoon boulder.

content.description: A forced line, but good climbing.  Starting left hand on the lip and right hand underneath climb out the fridge feature and top out at the end.  Awesome and unique compression climbing.
content.location: Just below El parasol project by 10 feet and just uphill from Fat Raccoon boulder.

content.description: Climb the prominent nose like arete from a stand start on the El Parasol Boulder.  Feels exposed.
content.location: El Parasol Boulder.  A couple hundred feet above the north shore beach on the westbluff and slightly north.

content.description: Start as for the fridge and go straight up.  Only a couple moves but fun.
content.location: Just below El Parasol project by 10 feet

content.description: Climb out the huge, steep roof on sloping ledges and small crimps.  Unlike most roofs at the lake, this actually has a few holds on it.
content.location: From the parking area, walk down to the bottom of the hill to a bench at the end of the wide gravel path.  Walk straight up the hill behind the bench to this huge roof.

content.description: From a sit, with your left hand on a crimp and your right in an undercling, climb the Fridge.
content.location: The Fridge Boulder, just above the Fat Raccoon Boulder and below the Vice Grip roof.

content.description: Start sitting on the far left side of the El Parasol boulder, Left hand on the left arete, Right hand in a juggy sidepull undercling.  Do a cruxy deadpoint to a good hold and then do a deceptively tricky topout up and right.  Avoid the detached block at the top.  Or don't.  It just doesn't matter.  Pretty fun.
content.location: El Parasol Boulder.  A couple hundred feet above the north shore beach on the westbluff and slightly north.

content.description: Massive boulder featuring a large, low roof.
